The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 16: Tata Steel has entered into an agreement with Nippon Steels subsidiary for the transfer of a special steel making technology. Tata Steel and Nippon Steel Hardfacing Company have signed an agreement for the transfer of overlay welding technology for the surface conditioning of steel rolls used at different steel making processes, a company statement said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 16: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) plans to set up a trading arm in the US to sell fuel from its refineries at Jamnagar. We always said that we wanted to be near the markets. Thats why we have our presence in Europe and the Far East, said Reliance CEO and president (oil and gas) P.M.S. Prasad.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 16: Hit by high fuel prices, the countrys airline companies have sought permission from the directorate general of foreign trade to import aviation turbine fuel (ATF), which will cut operating costs by at least ten per cent.                            
	 Calcutta, Sept. 16: Andrew Yule amp; Co Ltd will restructure its engineering and electrical divisions into two subsidiaries by the end of the current fiscal. The companys engineering and electrical divisions will be split into two separate firms  Yule Engineering Ltd and Yule Electrical Ltd.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 16: NMDC Ltd has proposed to acquire Hyderabad-based Sponge Iron India Ltd (SIIL) for about Rs 81 crore. It plans to invest around Rs 400-500 crore to make SIIL an integrated steel producing unit, a company official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 16: The states have asked the Centre to augment the public distribution system to contain inflation. They also demanded that their share in central taxes be raised to 50 per cent. At present, the states share in the divisible pool of the central taxes is 30.5 per cent.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 16: Textile manufacturer Welspun India will demerge its distribution and marketing business, and investment division into two separate entities.                                                                                                                         
